{"title":"IRIBA Working Paper 08: Mapping Corruption and its Institutional Determinants in Brazil","public_updated_at":"2014-01-01T00:00:00Z","details":{"body":[{"content_type":"text/govspeak","content":"## Abstract\n\n This paper provides an overview of the status, sources, and forms of corruption in Brazil. While the country outperforms many of its regional and developmental peers on various corruption-related indicators, corruption continues to plague many areas of public life, most notably in regional and state governments, political parties, parliament, and public procurement at all levels of government. After analysing what various metrics reveal about the character and level of corruption in Brazil, we examine how specific scandals have impacted anti-corruption initiatives in the country. We conclude with an overview of the various institutions oriented towards fighting corruption in Brazil, highlighting how systemic failures and deficiencies undermine the performance of accountability mechanisms, particularly at the punishment level. \n\n## Citation\n\nCarson, L.; Mota Prado, M. IRIBA Working Paper 08: Mapping Corruption and its Institutional Determinants in Brazil. International Research Initiative on Brazil and Africa (IRIBA), University of Manchester, Manchester, UK (2014) 45 pp.\n\n## Links\n\n[InlineAttachment:IRIBA_WP08_Mapping_Corruption_and_its_Institutional_Derminants_in_Brazil.pdf]\n"},{"content_type":"text/html","content":"<h2 id=\"abstract\">Abstract</h2>\n\n<p>This paper provides an overview of the status, sources, and forms of corruption in Brazil. While the country outperforms many of its regional and developmental peers on various corruption-related indicators, corruption continues to plague many areas of public life, most notably in regional and state governments, political parties, parliament, and public procurement at all levels of government. After analysing what various metrics reveal about the character and level of corruption in Brazil, we examine how specific scandals have impacted anti-corruption initiatives in the country. We conclude with an overview of the various institutions oriented towards fighting corruption in Brazil, highlighting how systemic failures and deficiencies undermine the performance of accountability mechanisms, particularly at the punishment level. </p>\n\n<h2 id=\"citation\">Citation</h2>\n\n<p>Carson, L.; Mota Prado, M. IRIBA Working Paper 08: Mapping Corruption and its Institutional Determinants in Brazil. International Research Initiative on Brazil and Africa (IRIBA), University of Manchester, Manchester, UK (2014) 45 pp.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"links\">Links</h2>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/57a089efed915d3cfd0004d6/IRIBA_WP08_Mapping_Corruption_and_its_Institutional_Derminants_in_Brazil.pdf\">IRIBA Working Paper 08: Mapping Corruption and its Institutional Determinants in Brazil</a></p>\n"}],"metadata":{"document_type":"dfid_research_output","bulk_published":true,"country":["BR"],"first_published_at":"2014-01-01","dfid_document_type":"working_paper","dfid_authors":["Carson, L.","Mota Prado, M."],"dfid_review_status":"unreviewed","dfid_theme":["economic_growth"]},"change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2014-01-01T00:00:00Z","note":"First published."}],"headers":[{"text":"Abstract","level":2,"id":"abstract"},{"text":"Citation","level":2,"id":"citation"},{"text":"Links","level":2,"id":"links"}],"attachments":[{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/57a089efed915d3cfd0004d6/IRIBA_WP08_Mapping_Corruption_and_its_Institutional_Derminants_in_Brazil.pdf","title":"IRIBA Working Paper 08: Mapping Corruption and its Institutional Determinants in Brazil","content_type":"application/pdf","updated_at":"2016-08-02T12:16:08+00:00","created_at":"2016-08-02T12:16:08+00:00","content_id":"fc21dad7-a3f9-4b47-b7ae-451bd03677de"}]},"routes":[{"path":"/dfid-research-outputs/iriba-working-paper-08-mapping-corruption-and-its-institution